<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p>Two <rs type="material" key="plumbum">lead</rs> (<seg cert="low">or <rs type="material" key="aes">bronze</rs></seg>) <rs type="objectType">tablet</rs>s each shaped rather like a shoe-heel (i. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.055</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.057</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.0027</measure>; ii. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.055</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.056</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.0023</measure>); probably a single piece of metal folded in half and later broken along this weakened line.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p> Each <rs type="execution" key="scalpro">scratched</rs> on one face, on the surface that would have been concealed by the fold.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Description of Letters</head>
<p> i. <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.007–0.01</measure>; ii. <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.005-0.007</measure>; in ii. <foreign lang="grc">Α</foreign> has [[crooked]] cross-bar; <foreign lang="grc">Ν</foreign> written backwards; <foreign lang="grc">Θ</foreign>  is diamond-shaped, which perhaps suggests second to third centuries A.D., but the lettering is too informal for confidence. Looks Roman rather than Hellenistic.</p>
</div>

<div type="description" n="date">
 <head>Date</head>

<p>     Probably <date notAfter="0400" notBefore="0001" exact="none" cert="low">Roman</date> (<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>). Many of the coins are first century B.C., but the hoard as a whole covers too wide a date range to offer a useful <term lang="la">terminus ante quem</term>.</p></div>

